# Frontend React

See `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/rules/frontend-qa.mdc` for the full QA gate. Cross-cutting rules: repo `.cursor/rules/engineering-workflow.mdc`.

## API

- Endpoints only in `src/apiConfig.js` — never hardcode `/api/...`
- Dev proxy: `package.json` → `"proxy": "http://localhost:5000"`
- When renaming legacy endpoints (e.g. `SF2`), add the new key, migrate call sites,
  then **comment out** the old alias (do not delete until Phase 8 is validated).

## Key routes

| Route | Page |
|-------|------|
| `/` | PortfolioPage |
| `/dashboard` | DashboardPage |
| `/news` | NewsPage |
| `/screener` | StockScreenerPage |
| `/admin` | AdminConsolePage |
| `/:ticker` | SummaryPage |
| `/:ticker/financials` | FinancialsPage |
| `/:ticker/insiders` | TickerDetailsPage (insider transactions) |
| `/columns` | NasdaqColumnsGrid (legacy fundamentals field glossary) |
| `/ticker/:ticker` | redirect → `/:ticker/insiders` |

## Free-first UX

- Empty states should link to `/admin` when cache or portfolio is empty.
- Show `meta.source` when present (`sqlite`, `sec_edgar`, `nasdaq`, `disabled`).
- Bootstrap/Reactstrap + DataGrid + ApexCharts; Redux only for screener state.

## High-density UI

- Preserve information-dense grids and compact layouts (research, screener, industry) — do not inflate spacing or strip columns for aesthetics.
- Heatmaps and conditional formatting via `heatMap.js` / `scoringColors.js`; metric keys from `config/metricRegistry.js`.
- No duplicate metric thresholds or composite scoring in page components.

## Performance (grids & screener)

- Memoize column defs and handlers; use stable dataset keys — **never `JSON.stringify(rows)` as a memo dependency**.
- Heavy stats (`columnMinMax`, percentiles): cache per dataset id (`heatmapCache.js` pattern).
- Profile before adding new memo/cache layers; precompute row heat styles in `useMemo`, not per-cell on sort.

## Tests

- Unit: `npm test -- --watchAll=false`
- Full QA: `npm run qa:frontend`
